{"schema":"algviz/1","title":"Word Search II (Trie + DFS)","topic":"tries","code":["Node root = Build(words);","for (int r = 0; r < rows; r++)","  for (int c = 0; c < cols; c++)","    Dfs(board, r, c, root, results);","","void Dfs(board, r, c, Node node, results) {","    char ch = board[r][c];","    if (ch == '#') return;            // on current path","    Node? next = node.Children[ch - 'a'];","    if (next is null) return;         // PRUNE: dead prefix","    if (next.Word is not null) {","        results.Add(next.Word);","        next.Word = null;             // de-dupe","    }","    board[r][c] = '#';                // mark visited","    Dfs(board, r+1, c, next, results);","    Dfs(board, r-1, c, next, results);","    Dfs(board, r, c+1, next, results);","    Dfs(board, r, c-1, next, results);","    board[r][c] = ch;                 // restore (backtrack)","}"],"structures":{"board":{"type":"grid","label":"board (# = on current DFS path)"},"trie":{"type":"graph","label":"trie of all words (edge = next char; * = word end)"}},"frames":[{"line":1,"caption":"Build one trie of all words, then DFS every board cell. Root edges that exist: o, p, e, r — the four first letters.","note":"Before any board walk we build ONE trie from every target word, storing the whole word string on the node where it ends. This is the move that beats running a single-word DFS once per word: shared prefixes across words collapse into one path, and at every board cell the trie answers \"could any word continue this way?\" in O(1). Building costs O(total characters in words).","vars":{"words":"[oath, pea, eat, rain]","results":"[]"},"result":null,"states":{"board":{"type":"grid","rows":4,"cols":4,"cells":[{"key":"r0c0","value":"o"},{"key":"r0c1","value":"a"},{"key":"r0c2","value":"a"},{"key":"r0c3","value":"n"},{"key":"r1c0","value":"e"},{"key":"r1c1","value":"t"},{"key":"r1c2","value":"a"},{"key":"r1c3","value":"e"},{"key":"r2c0","value":"i"},{"key":"r2c1","value":"h"},{"key":"r2c2","value":"k"},{"key":"r2c3","value":"r"},{"key":"r3c0","value":"i"},{"key":"r3c1","value":"f"},{"key":"r3c2","value":"l"},{"key":"r3c3","value":"v"}]},"trie":{"type":"graph","directed":true,"nodes":[{"key":"root","value":"root","x":50,"y":6,"highlight":"current"},{"key":"o","value":"o","x":14,"y":30,"highlight":"muted"},{"key":"oa","value":"a","x":14,"y":52,"highlight":"muted"},{"key":"oat","value":"t","x":14,"y":74,"highlight":"muted"},{"key":"oath","value":"oath*","x":14,"y":94,"highlight":"visited"},{"key":"p","value":"p","x":38,"y":30,"highlight":"muted"},{"key":"pe","value":"e","x":38,"y":52,"highlight":"muted"},{"key":"pea","value":"pea*","x":38,"y":74,"highlight":"visited"},{"key":"e","value":"e","x":62,"y":30,"highlight":"muted"},{"key":"ea","value":"a","x":62,"y":52,"highlight":"muted"},{"key":"eat","value":"eat*","x":62,"y":74,"highlight":"visited"},{"key":"r","value":"r","x":86,"y":30,"highlight":"muted"},{"key":"ra","value":"a","x":86,"y":52,"highlight":"muted"},{"key":"rai","value":"i","x":86,"y":74,"highlight":"muted"},{"key":"rain","value":"rain*","x":86,"y":94,"highlight":"visited"}],"edges":[{"from":"root","to":"o","highlight":"muted"},{"from":"o","to":"oa","highlight":"muted"},{"from":"oa","to":"oat","highlight":"muted"},{"from":"oat","to":"oath","highlight":"muted"},{"from":"root","to":"p","highlight":"muted"},{"from":"p","to":"pe","highlight":"muted"},{"from":"pe","to":"pea","highlight":"muted"},{"from":"root","to":"e","highlight":"muted"},{"from":"e","to":"ea","highlight":"muted"},{"from":"ea","to":"eat","highlight":"muted"},{"from":"root","to":"r","highlight":"muted"},{"from":"r","to":"ra","highlight":"muted"},{"from":"ra","to":"rai","highlight":"muted"},{"from":"rai","to":"rain","highlight":"muted"}]}}},{"line":9,"caption":"Start a DFS at (0,1)='a'. Look up child 'a' of the trie root.","note":"The cell's letter might be a live trie edge, so the prefix is still viable for some word — descend into the trie child and keep the board DFS alive. Walking the board and the trie in lockstep is the whole technique: every grid step is matched by exactly one trie step, and the trie does the pruning for free.","vars":{"words":"[oath, pea, eat, rain]","results":"[]","start":"(0,1)","ch":"'a'"},"result":null,"states":{"board":{"type":"grid","rows":4,"cols":4,"cells":[{"key":"r0c0","value":"o"},{"key":"r0c1","value":"a","highlight":"compared"},{"key":"r0c2","value":"a"},{"key":"r0c3","value":"n"},{"key":"r1c0","value":"e"},{"key":"r1c1","value":"t"},{"key":"r1c2","value":"a"},{"key":"r1c3","value":"e"},{"key":"r2c0","value":"i"},{"key":"r2c1","value":"h"},{"key":"r2c2","value":"k"},{"key":"r2c3","value":"r"},{"key":"r3c0","value":"i"},{"key":"r3c1","value":"f"},{"key":"r3c2","value":"l"},{"key":"r3c3","value":"v"}]},"trie":{"type":"graph","directed":true,"nodes":[{"key":"root","value":"root","x":50,"y":6,"highlight":"current"},{"key":"o","value":"o","x":14,"y":30,"highlight":"muted"},{"key":"oa","value":"a","x":14,"y":52,"highlight":"muted"},{"key":"oat","value":"t","x":14,"y":74,"highlight":"muted"},{"key":"oath","value":"oath*","x":14,"y":94,"highlight":"visited"},{"key":"p","value":"p","x":38,"y":30,"highlight":"muted"},{"key":"pe","value":"e","x":38,"y":52,"highlight":"muted"},{"key":"pea","value":"pea*","x":38,"y":74,"highlight":"visited"},{"key":"e","value":"e","x":62,"y":30,"highlight":"muted"},{"key":"ea","value":"a","x":62,"y":52,"highlight":"muted"},{"key":"eat","value":"eat*","x":62,"y":74,"highlight":"visited"},{"key":"r","value":"r","x":86,"y":30,"highlight":"muted"},{"key":"ra","value":"a","x":86,"y":52,"highlight":"muted"},{"key":"rai","value":"i","x":86,"y":74,"highlight":"muted"},{"key":"rain","value":"rain*","x":86,"y":94,"highlight":"visited"}],"edges":[{"from":"root","to":"o","highlight":"muted"},{"from":"o","to":"oa","highlight":"muted"},{"from":"oa","to":"oat","highlight":"muted"},{"from":"oat","to":"oath","highlight":"muted"},{"from":"root","to":"p","highlight":"muted"},{"from":"p","to":"pe","highlight":"muted"},{"from":"pe","to":"pea","highlight":"muted"},{"from":"root","to":"e","highlight":"muted"},{"from":"e","to":"ea","highlight":"muted"},{"from":"ea","to":"eat","highlight":"muted"},{"from":"root","to":"r","highlight":"muted"},{"from":"r","to":"ra","highlight":"muted"},{"from":"ra","to":"rai","highlight":"muted"},{"from":"rai","to":"rain","highlight":"muted"}]}}},{"line":10,"caption":"root has no child 'a' (no word starts with a) → next is null → PRUNE. The whole 'a' region is abandoned in O(1).","note":"The heart of the algorithm. Look up the cell's letter as a child of the current trie node; if it is null, NO stored word has this prefix, so we abandon this branch immediately — `if (next is null) return;`. Here the board cell exists but the trie has no matching edge, so an entire region of the grid is ruled out in O(1) before any deep DFS. Without this line the search degrades toward brute force, re-exploring dead prefixes.","vars":{"words":"[oath, pea, eat, rain]","results":"[]","start":"(0,1)","ch":"'a'","next":"null"},"result":null,"states":{"board":{"type":"grid","rows":4,"cols":4,"cells":[{"key":"r0c0","value":"o"},{"key":"r0c1","value":"a","highlight":"muted"},{"key":"r0c2","value":"a"},{"key":"r0c3","value":"n"},{"key":"r1c0","value":"e"},{"key":"r1c1","value":"t"},{"key":"r1c2","value":"a"},{"key":"r1c3","value":"e"},{"key":"r2c0","value":"i"},{"key":"r2c1","value":"h"},{"key":"r2c2","value":"k"},{"key":"r2c3","value":"r"},{"key":"r3c0","value":"i"},{"key":"r3c1","value":"f"},{"key":"r3c2","value":"l"},{"key":"r3c3","value":"v"}]},"trie":{"type":"graph","directed":true,"nodes":[{"key":"root","value":"root","x":50,"y":6,"highlight":"current"},{"key":"o","value":"o","x":14,"y":30,"highlight":"muted"},{"key":"oa","value":"a","x":14,"y":52,"highlight":"muted"},{"key":"oat","value":"t","x":14,"y":74,"highlight":"muted"},{"key":"oath","value":"oath*","x":14,"y":94,"highlight":"visited"},{"key":"p","value":"p","x":38,"y":30,"highlight":"muted"},{"key":"pe","valu